chat_messages.text:
 To set the default font size for alignment environments (like `align`, `flalign`, `align*`, etc.) throughout your entire LaTeX document, you can add the following code to your preamble (the area before `\begin{document}`):

```latex
\usepackage{etoolbox}

% For align environment
\AtBeginEnvironment{align}{\small}
\AtBeginEnvironment{align*}{\small}

% For flalign environment
\AtBeginEnvironment{flalign}{\small}
\AtBeginEnvironment{flalign*}{\small}

% For other alignment environments if needed
\AtBeginEnvironment{eqnarray}{\small}
\AtBeginEnvironment{eqnarray*}{\small}
\AtBeginEnvironment{gather}{\small}
\AtBeginEnvironment{gather*}{\small}
\AtBeginEnvironment{multline}{\small}
\AtBeginEnvironment{multline*}{\small}
```

This requires the `etoolbox` package and uses the `\AtBeginEnvironment` command to automatically apply the size change when the environment begins.

You can replace `\small` with any of the other size commands:
- `\footnotesize` (smaller than small)
- `\scriptsize` (smaller than footnotesize)
- `\tiny` (smallest standard size)

If you want to affect all math environments including inline math, you could alternatively use:

```latex
\everymath{\footnotesize}
\everydisplay{\footnotesize}
```

These commands change the size of all inline math expressions (`$...$`) and displayed math (`$$...$$` and all AMS environments).

Remember to include the appropriate packages for any math environments you're using:
```latex
\usepackage{amsmath} % For advanced math environments
\usepackage{etoolbox} % For the \AtBeginEnvironment command
```

