 To make text bold within a `\begin{scope}` block in TikZ/PGF, you have several options:

1. **Add bold font to the scope options:**

```latex
\begin{scope}[font=\bfseries]
   % Your TikZ content here
   \node at (0,0) {This text will be bold};
\end{scope}
```

2. **Set bold font for all nodes in the scope:**

```latex
\begin{scope}[every node/.style={font=\bfseries}]
   % Your TikZ content here
   \node at (0,0) {This text will be bold};
\end{scope}
```

3. **Combine bold with size changes:**

```latex
\begin{scope}[every node/.style={font=\Large\bfseries}]
   % Your TikZ content here
   \node at (0,0) {This text will be large and bold};
\end{scope}
```

4. **Use a text formatting command inside each node:**

```latex
\begin{scope}
   % Your TikZ content here
   \node at (0,0) {\textbf{This text will be bold}};
\end{scope}
```

5. **For math content, use `\mathbf` for bold math:**

```latex
\begin{scope}
   % Your TikZ content here
   \node at (0,0) {$\mathbf{E = mc^2}$};
\end{scope}
```

If you want to apply both larger size and bold font, simply combine the commands:

```latex
\begin{scope}[every node/.style={font=\Huge\bfseries}]
   % Your TikZ content here
   \node at (0,0) {Very large and bold text};
\end{scope}
```

This will make all text within the scope appear in bold and at the specified size.

